{"key":"post-10842470","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10842470</id>\n<content>The rye won't EVER germinate if you follow the tek and rinse in hot tap water.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Soaking less than four hours can lead to burst kernels when you boil or PC because too much water is absorbed in too short a time.&amp;nbsp; Over 24 hours soaking and the bacterial endospores that have germinated will have made a few billion new endospores, defeating the purpose since at least some of them will survive the PC.&amp;nbsp; Long soak times actually lead to more contamination, not less.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you soak 4 hours, you might need to boil twenty minutes to get the grains to double their original size.&amp;nbsp; If you soak 24 hours, you only need to boil for a couple of minutes to heat up the grains so they'll flash off the additional moisture as steam, once you drain them.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>10842308</prev>\n<first>10842238</first>\n<last>10842470</last>\n<when>1250048391</when>\n<utime>08/12/09 06:39 AM</utime>\n</post>"}